{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "This principle emphasizes the importance of fairness in the distribution of resources and access to health care services.",
    "In practical medical settings, justice can be translated into unbiased decision-making, equal opportunity for treatment, and eradication of any form of discrimination.Justice is an important aspect regarding the use of AI in medicine.",
    "Owing to the risk of bias due to unrepresentative training data, for example, treatment recommendations from the use of AI in medicine could lead to disadvantages for different groups or individuals, directly conflicting with the principle of justice [50].",
    "Furthermore, access to the technology itself could be limited, for example, by economic means, thereby potentially perpetuating existing inequalities in access to advanced medical technologies [35].",
    "This potential for injustice can be further exacerbated if an increasing prevalence of AI in medical practice is anticipated.Owing to the substantial risk of injustice with the use of AI in medicine, medical education should include teaching the principle of justice in the context of AI."
  ],
